  <div class="section">
#+END_HTML

** Exact Equations
   :PROPERTIES:
   :CUSTOM_ID: exact-equations
   :END:

Start with a family of curves

#+BEGIN_HTML
  <div style="color:rgba(128,0,62,1);">
#+END_HTML

$f\left( {x,y} \right) = c$

#+BEGIN_HTML
  </div>
#+END_HTML

differential equation is of the form

#+BEGIN_HTML
  <div style="color:rgba(128,0,62,1);">
#+END_HTML

 d f = 0 ∂ f ∂ x dx + ∂ t ∂ y dy = 0

#+BEGIN_HTML
  </div>
#+END_HTML

Now let's begin with the differential equation

#+BEGIN_HTML
  <div style="color:rgba(128,0,62,1);">
#+END_HTML

$M\left( {x,y} \right){dx} + N\left( {x,y} \right){dy} = 0$

#+BEGIN_HTML
  </div>
#+END_HTML

If there happens to exist a function

#+BEGIN_HTML
  <div style="color:rgba(128,0,62,1);">
#+END_HTML

$f\left( {x,y} \right)$

#+BEGIN_HTML
  </div>
#+END_HTML

such that

#+BEGIN_HTML
  <div style="color:rgba(128,0,62,1);">
#+END_HTML

$\frac{\partial f}{\partial x} = M$

#+BEGIN_HTML
  </div>
#+END_HTML

and

#+BEGIN_HTML
  <div style="color:rgba(128,0,62,1);">
#+END_HTML

$\frac{\partial f}{\partial y} = N$

#+BEGIN_HTML
  </div>
#+END_HTML

then df can be written as

#+BEGIN_HTML
  <div style="color:rgba(128,0,62,1);">
#+END_HTML

$\frac{\partial f}{\partial x}{dx} + \frac{\partial f}{\partial y}{dy} = 0$

#+BEGIN_HTML
  </div>
#+END_HTML

#+BEGIN_HTML
  <div style="color:rgba(128,0,62,1);">
#+END_HTML

$df = 0$

#+BEGIN_HTML
  </div>
#+END_HTML

General solution is

#+BEGIN_HTML
  <div style="color:rgba(128,0,62,1);">
#+END_HTML

$f\left( {x,y} \right) = c$

#+BEGIN_HTML
  </div>
#+END_HTML

Expression

#+BEGIN_HTML
  <div style="color:rgba(128,0,62,1);">
#+END_HTML

$M{dx} + N{dy}$

#+BEGIN_HTML
  </div>
#+END_HTML

is the exact differential equation

the exact solution of a given fanction can sometimes be determined by
inspection.

for the curve

Curve example 1:

#+BEGIN_HTML
  <div style="color:rgba(0,0,0,1);">
#+END_HTML

$xy = 0$

#+BEGIN_HTML
  </div>
#+END_HTML

#+BEGIN_HTML
  <div style="color:rgba(0,0,0,1);">
#+END_HTML

$y{dx} + x{dy} = 0$

#+BEGIN_HTML
  </div>
#+END_HTML

Cure example 2:

#+BEGIN_HTML
  <div style="color:rgba(0,0,0,1);">
#+END_HTML

$\frac{x}{y} = 0$

#+BEGIN_HTML
  </div>
#+END_HTML

#+BEGIN_HTML
  <div style="color:rgba(0,0,0,1);">
#+END_HTML

$\frac{1}{y}{dx} - \frac{x}{y^{2}}{dy} = 0$

#+BEGIN_HTML
  </div>
#+END_HTML

** A test for exactness and a method to finding function f
   :PROPERTIES:
   :CUSTOM_ID: a-test-for-exactness-and-a-method-to-finding-function-f
   :END:

If a function f exists for a given exact differential equation

#+BEGIN_HTML
  <div style="color:rgba(0,0,0,1);">
#+END_HTML

$M{dx} + N{dy} = 0$

#+BEGIN_HTML
  </div>
#+END_HTML

then the mixed second partial derivatives of f are equal assuming f is
continuous

#+BEGIN_HTML
  <div style="color:rgba(0,0,0,1);">
#+END_HTML

$\frac{\partial^{2}f}{\partial y\partial x} = \frac{\partial^{2}f}{\partial x\partial y}$

#+BEGIN_HTML
  </div>
#+END_HTML

this yields

#+BEGIN_HTML
  <div style="color:rgba(0,0,0,1);">
#+END_HTML

$\frac{\partial M}{\partial y} = \frac{\partial N}{\partial x}$

#+BEGIN_HTML
  </div>
#+END_HTML

to be a necessary condition for exactness

To construct a function f that satisfies the given exact solution

start by integrating

#+BEGIN_HTML
  <div style="color:rgba(0,0,0,1);">
#+END_HTML

$\frac{\partial f}{\partial x} = M$

#+BEGIN_HTML
  </div>
#+END_HTML

#+BEGIN_HTML
  <div style="color:rgba(0,0,0,1);">
#+END_HTML

$f = \int M{dx} + g\left( y \right)$

#+BEGIN_HTML
  </div>
#+END_HTML

the integration constant is a function of y since it must disappear when
differentiating with respect to ×

Our problem is now reduced to finding a function of y g (y ) such that f
satisfies the equation

#+BEGIN_HTML
  <div style="color:rgba(0,0,0,1);">
#+END_HTML

$\frac{\partial f}{\partial y} = N$

#+BEGIN_HTML
  </div>
#+END_HTML

Differentiating the last equation with respect to y

#+BEGIN_HTML
  <div style="color:rgba(0,0,0,1);">
#+END_HTML

$\frac{\partial}{\partial y}\int M{dx} + g^{1}\left( g \right) = N$

#+BEGIN_HTML
  </div>
#+END_HTML

#+BEGIN_HTML
  <div style="color:rgba(0,0,0,1);">
#+END_HTML

$g'\left( y \right) = N - \frac{\partial}{\partial y}\int M{dx}$

#+BEGIN_HTML
  </div>
#+END_HTML

#+BEGIN_HTML
  <div style="color:rgba(0,0,0,1);">
#+END_HTML

$g\left( y \right) = \int\left( {N - \frac{\partial}{\partial y}\int M{dx}} \right){dy}$

#+BEGIN_HTML
  </div>
#+END_HTML

provided the integnand here is a function of y (derivative of the
integnand with respect to × is o)

** Statement:
   :PROPERTIES:
   :CUSTOM_ID: statement
   :END:

an equation is exact if and only if

#+BEGIN_HTML
  <div style="color:rgba(0,0,0,1);">
#+END_HTML

$\frac{\partial M}{\partial y} = \frac{\partial N}{\partial x}$

#+BEGIN_HTML
  </div>
#+END_HTML

the general solution is

#+BEGIN_HTML
  <div style="color:rgba(0,0,0,1);">
#+END_HTML

$f\left( {x,y} \right) = c$

#+BEGIN_HTML
  </div>
#+END_HTML

#+BEGIN_HTML
  </div>
#+END_HTML
